R1: In such a small area, it is inappropriate to do things that require people to leave that zone, that happens with carrying big objects or mopping the floor. As for vacuum cleaning, it seems to be nighttime and it would greatly disturb any social interaction between the people within the circle.
R2: I don't believe that the robot would be sufficiently near people in order to effectively start a conversation. Vacuum cleaning would be inappropriate because music is playing, and since there's a social gathering, mopping the floor would also be inappropriate.
R3: There's some space in order to do things, all actions are okay. Plus, there's only one person in the room so it seems like an appropriate moment to do all kinds of actions.
R4: It seems it would be okay to start a conversation, since there's a circle of people ahead. Because of that, the robot shouldn't mop the floor nor vacuum clean.
R5: There are no people in the direction of the arrow, therefore bringing food or drinks seems inappropriate. Likewise, the robot can't really start a conversation with the sofa in the middle.
R6: Starting a conversation seems to be the number one action to do here. Therefore, the robot shouldn't be doing any kind of cleaning nor carrying objects, especially big ones.
R7: Apart from picking up stuff, mopping or vacuum cleaning would greatly disturb the humans, the same happens with carrying big objects.
R8: Assuming the person sitting in the couch is relaxing but awake, it seems appropriate for the robot to have a conversation either with people near it or with the person in the couch. Cleaning activities shouldn't be done in this situation.
R9: Vacuum cleaning, mopping the floor and carrying objects would disturb the humans within the circle. Picking up stuff and carrying food or drinks seems okay.
R10: There isn't any person in the direction of the arrow, therefore it is inappropriate to start a conversation. Carrying objects seem to not make much sense too, because of the short distance. It's also inappropriate to carry food or drinks. Mopping the floor is the only neutral action in my opinion, since it wouldn't disturb people.
R11: No actions are appropriate, since the robot has an obstacle in place (the couch).
R12: Assuming the robot is leaving the gathering, it seems okay to carry small objects. I'm not sure about cleaning. It is inappriate to start a conversation, the robot should be instead ending it.
R13: It seems to be okay to be cleaning, the robot is sufficiently far from the people in the room, because of that, it can't really start a conversation and it shouldn't carry food and drinks.
R14: There are no gatherings in the room, people are by themselves, so it seems to be appropriate to perform cleaning activities the most. The robot is also not sufficiently near people in order to start a conversation.
R15: Mopping the floor is not appropriate, since the dog would undo all the cleaning done with his random walks. Vacuum cleaning seems to be okay in this situation. There also the possibility to carry small objects like toys for the animal.
R16: I don't think it's okay to mop or vacuum clean in the circle. Since there's only one person in the circle, the most appropriate action would be to start a conversation, but that's not available. Picking up stuff should be fine.
R17: There are no humans in the direction of the arrow, therefore starting a conversation does not make sense. For the same reason, carrying food or drinks does not make much sense. The other actions are neutral.
R18: It would be better to do actions that are silent in nature, because there is a person lying in the sofa, therefore vacuum cleaning is very inappropriate. Mopping the floor and picking up stuff is silent enough and shouldn't disturb the humans around.
R19: There are no people in the room, it's okay to perform cleaning activities and carrying all sorts of objects.
R20: There are no humans in the direction of the arrow, so it doesn't make sense to start a conversation. It's also inappropriate to carry objects, since there's not much space to travel.
